# RouteMind Agent Rules

You are working on RouteMind, a route optimization and navigation-style web platform.

Your job is not to make partial improvements.
Your job is to finish the project properly.

## Non-negotiable requirements

The project is only considered complete when the full real browser flow works end-to-end.

That includes all of the following:

- registration works in the UI
- login works in the UI
- user is really written to SQLite
- token is stored correctly
- /me works
- logout works

- country selection works
- address-based input works
- city / street / house number flow works
- autocomplete works
- geocoding works

- optimization works
- scenarios work
- history works

- the map visibly renders
- markers visibly render
- the route polyline visibly renders
- map style switching works
- satellite/standard modes work if implemented

- walking and driving must actually change route and ETA
- displayed route must use real routing logic
- no straight-line fallback for real routes
- no fake ETA for real places

- dark/light theme must remain usable
- no fake or misleading frontend errors
- real backend errors must be surfaced honestly

## Critical behavior rules

- Do not report “almost done”.
- Do not give partial completion summaries as final results.
- Do not use template/example cities unrelated to the user’s real context.
- Do not claim something is fixed unless you verified it.
- Do not hide broken functionality behind nicer wording.
- Do not keep dead or half-migrated logic if it causes inconsistency.

## Map / routing rules

- Visible route geometry must not come from Euclidean distance or straight-line approximation.
- Real addresses must be geocoded into real coordinates.
- Displayed route and ETA must come from a real routing source/provider.
- The optimization layer may determine stop order, but displayed navigation must be real.

## Browser verification rules

Before saying anything is fixed, verify in the actual app flow:

1. open the browser UI
2. register a real user
3. log in
4. verify user row is written to SQLite
5. enter real addresses
6. geocode them
7. optimize a route
8. verify map is visible
9. verify route is visible
10. verify ETA is realistic
11. switch walking/driving and verify the route/time changes
12. save/load scenario
13. verify history
14. verify theme switching

## Reporting rules

When reporting back, always include:

1. exact files changed
2. exact bugs fixed
3. exact things verified manually in browser
4. exact things verified automatically
5. anything still not finished

Never say "fixed" unless the full real flow was verified.
